title: Apple Service Diagnostic disk
description:
This is version 2.5.7.

I know it is not the current one, but any version is better than none if it works.

Been tried successfully on a G5 PPC. 

Am sure it will not work on an Intel as the program is some 3 - 4 years old.

Burn the downloaded .dmg file onto a CD using Disk Utility from the Utilities folder in your Applications. 

Insert the CD and restart, also holding down the C key. The application window then opens. Out of interest it took about 1 hour to carry out the tests on a G5.
